 President Muhammadu Buhari on Sunday finally signed the African Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA), which is the world’s largest free trade area, with 54 countries and 1.2 billion people. According to the United Nations (UN) Deputy Secretary-General Ms Amina Mohammed, the #AfCFTA would bring the promise of trade-led economic growth closer to reality for entrepreneurs, industrialists, investors, innovators and service suppliers.     This morning in Niamey, Niger, I had the honour of signing the agreement establishing the African Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA), on behalf of Nigeria. I wish to assure you that Nigeria shall sustain its strong leadership role in Africa, in the implementation of the AfCFTA. pic.twitter.com/G35yydVDGE — Muhammadu Buhari (@MBuhari) July 7, 2019 https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js The #AfCFTA, which Nigeria joined today, is world’s largest free trade area, with 54 countries and 1.2 bn people. It’ll bring the promise of trade-led economic growth closer to reality for entrepreneurs, industrialists, investors, innovators and service suppliers, @UN’s DSG says. pic.twitter.com/8sfzgJma5Y — Bashir Ahmad (@BashirAhmaad) July 7, 2019 https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js   President @MBuhari signing the Agreement Establishing the African Continental Free Trade Area (#AfCFTA), at the opening of the 12th Extraordinary Session of the Assembly of African Union Heads of State and Govt, in Niamey, Niger Republic, July 7, 2019 #AUSummit pic.twitter.com/s3Bfps3Y6c — Bashir Ahmad (@BashirAhmaad) July 7, 2019 https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js  SOURCE: Bashir Ahmad @BashirAhmaad The post PHOTO: Buhari Finally Signs African Continental Free Trade Area appeared first on Independent Newspapers Nigeria. Source: Independent